This article is a proclamation issued by the President of the United States on March 22, 2018. The proclamation discusses the imposition of tariffs on steel mill articles imported into the United States. The President concurs with the Secretary of Commerce's finding that these imports threaten to impair the national security of the United States. The proclamation exempts certain countries, including Canada, Mexico, Australia, Argentina, South Korea, Brazil, and the European Union, from the tariff and states that ongoing discussions will continue with these countries to address the threat to national security. The proclamation also mentions the importance of addressing global excess capacity in steel production. The President emphasizes that the tariff is an important first step in protecting the domestic steel industry and that further discussions and alternative means to address the threat will be considered. The proclamation also addresses measures to prevent transshipment and increased exports of steel articles to the United States.